1 payments may be made based upon additional valid claims submitted. The
2 State Treasurer shall, between the fifth and twentieth day of each month,
3 notify the Director of Administrative Services of the amount of funds
4 available in the General Fund and the Education Future Fund for payment
5 purposes. The director shall, upon receiving such certification, draw
6 warrants against such funds as appropriated.
7 (b) If the General Fund appropriations for special education
8 approved by the Legislature, minus the amounts set aside pursuant to
9 subsection (5) of this section, are insufficient to reimburse eighty
10 percent of the total allowable excess costs for all special education
11 programs and support services for any school fiscal year:
12 (i) Such allowable excess costs shall be reimbursed from the General
13 Fund appropriations for special education approved by the Legislature,
14 minus the amounts set aside pursuant to subsection (5) of this section,
15 on a pro rata basis at the maximum rate of reimbursement such
16 appropriations will allow as determined by the department; and
17 (ii) The remainder of the eighty percent reimbursement of such
18 allowable excess costs shall be paid from the Education Future Fund.
19 (5) Residential settings described in subdivision (10)(c) of section
20 79-215 shall be reimbursed for the educational services, including
21 special education services and support services, in an amount determined
22 pursuant to the average per pupil cost of the service agency.
23 Reimbursements pursuant to this section shall be made from funds set
24 aside for such purpose within sixty days after receipt of a reimbursement
25 request submitted in the manner required by the department and including
26 any documentation required by the department for educational services
27 that have been provided, except that if there are not any funds available
28 for the remainder of the state fiscal year for such reimbursements, the
29 reimbursement shall occur within thirty days after the beginning of the
30 immediately following state fiscal year. The department may audit any
31 required documentation and subtract any payments made in error from
