1 future reimbursements. The department shall set aside separate amounts
2 from the appropriations for special education approved by the Legislature
3 for reimbursements pursuant to this subsection for students receiving
4 special education services and for students receiving support services
5 for each state fiscal year. The amounts set aside for each purpose shall
6 be based on estimates of the reimbursements to be requested during the
7 state fiscal year and shall not be less than the total amount of
8 reimbursements requested in the prior state fiscal year plus any unpaid
9 requests from the prior state fiscal year.
10 (6) For each school district that received a payment pursuant to the
11 Extraordinary Increase in Special Education Expenditures Act in the
12 school fiscal year for which special education expenditures were
13 reimbursed pursuant to subsection (3) of this section, an amount equal to
14 such payment shall be subtracted from the reimbursement calculated
15 pursuant to subsection (3) of this section and such amount shall be
16 transferred to the Education Future Fund.
17 (7) The allowable and reimbursable costs for special education and
18 support services shall include substitute service costs directly
19 associated with special education programs. Each school district shall
20 provide special education staff with four days of professional leave per
21 year, supported by substitute personnel. Such leave shall be used onsite
22 for the sole purpose of completing essential documentation for students
23 receiving special education services on such staff's caseload.
24 (8) (7) On or before November 15 of each year, the department shall
25 submit to the Governor, the Appropriations Committee of the Legislature,
26 and the Education Committee of the Legislature:
27 (a) The total allowable excess costs for all special education
28 programs and support services for all school districts, cooperatives of
29 school districts, and educational service units; and
30 (b) The total reimbursements requested pursuant to subsection (5) of
31 this section for the most recently completed school fiscal year.
